{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9cd51d01-1e49-444c-b388-17491168ce15","content":"Your tutorial is likely based on **Xamarin.Forms**, not .NET MAUI. The concepts are similar but there are key differences:\n\n**1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`**\nIn .NET MAUI, pages **respect the safe area by default** on iOS — content is automatically padded away from the notch/Dynamic Island. You typically don't need to set this explicitly. The platform-specific still exists but under the MAUI namespace:\n\n```\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\n**2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`**\nThis is correct for .NET MAUI. Use it on a layout (like a `Grid`) when you want content — such as a background image — to extend behind the notch/status bar:\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n**In summary:** For .NET 10 MAUI, you likely don't need `UseSafeArea` at all (it's the default). Use `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` only on layouts where you intentionally want to bleed into the unsafe area.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a19b5895-b12c-4e9c-8a4a-d0c979dade21","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid for background images\n\nLet me check what I know about these APIs in .NET MAUI, particularly for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI (which evolved from Xamarin.Forms), the safe area handling changed:\n\n1. **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea`** - This was a Xamarin.Forms iOS platform-specific. In .NET MAUI, this was replaced. In .NET MAUI, the safe area is handled differently. The correct approach in MAUI is to use `Page.IgnoreSafeArea` or the padding is automatically applied. Actually, let me think more carefully.\n\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd use the iOS-specific namespace to access `UseSafeArea`, but in .NET MAUI, safe area handling is built into the framework differently. I need to clarify what the current approach is for .NET 10 MAUI specifically. I'm realizing the user's example is using Xamarin.Forms syntax, but for .NET MAUI the approach is slightly different—pages automatically respect the safe area by default, and while the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` platform-specific still exists under the MAUI namespace, you'd typically use `IgnoreSafeArea` on layouts if you want content to extend behind notches or other unsafe areas.","outputTokens":1193,"requestId":"100A:341527:155BD12:1813176:69FD37A2"},"id":"d4392e8b-038f-40f3-af06-be0d8d08dd55","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:09:14.632Z","parentId":"aa482387-3a89-4fe5-9861-5afabe8bcd5d"}
